HOUSE BILL 1202
F1 6lr3334
By: Delegates Acevero, Alston, Lewis, Martinez, Stinnett, Woods, and Young
Introduced and read first time: February 11, 2026
Assigned to: Ways and Means
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Public Schools – Content Standards, Curriculum, and Bullying Policies –
3 Culture and History of Palestine
4 FOR the purpose of requiring the State Board of Education to develop certain content
5 standards regarding the culture and history of Palestine to be included in certain
6 State standards for social studies; requiring the Department, in collaboration with
7 certain stakeholders, to develop certain curriculum guides and instructional
8 resources regarding the culture and history of Palestine in alignment with certain
9 content standards; requiring each county board of education to develop, in
10 collaboration with certain stakeholders, certain curriculum guides; requiring each
11 public school to include Palestinian culture and history in the social studies
12 curriculum beginning in a certain school year; altering the requirements for a certain
13 model policy regarding bullying, harassment, or intimidation to expressly require
14 the inclusion of conduct motivated by an anti–Palestinian bias; requiring the
15 Department to review certain content standards and frameworks in social studies to
16 make a certain determination for a certain purpose; and generally relating to the
17 Palestinian culture and history education and content and curriculum standards.
18 BY adding to
19 Article – Education
20 Section 4–111.5
21 Annotated Code of Maryland
22 (2025 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
23 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
24 Article – Education
25 Section 7–424(a)(1) and (2) and 7–424.1(a) and (c)
26 Annotated Code of Maryland
27 (2025 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
28 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
